11/06/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Former Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy will be appointed as a chief consultant on NATO integration, Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski said on Friday (June 8th), during a meeting with Passy in Skopje. 
Gruevski explained that Passy would be invaluable in helping Macedonia avoid some of the mistakes Bulgaria made in its accession process. 
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV, Focus, BNR- 08/06/07)
